{@noteanchor{1 ms. has instead:} arise
}  from the water. The leopard seized the ibex and the wild sheep and took them to the mountains.


@(A.244 = 244-248) A fifth time they threw fish spawn (?) into the river. The sorcerer made a gazelle kid come out from the water. Wise Woman @wPN{Saŋburu}, however, made a tiger and a …… lion come out from the water. The tiger and the …… lion seized the gazelle kid and 
{took
} 
{@noteanchor{1 ms. has instead:} dragged
}  them to the forest. What happened made the face of the sorcerer darken, made his mind confused.


@(A.249 = 249-254) Wise Woman @wPN{Saŋburu} said to him: @q[Sajburu,Ur-jiri-nuna]{“Sorcerer, you do have magical powers, but where is your sense? How on earth could you think of going to do sorcery at @wSN{Ereš}, which is the city of @wDN{Nisaba}, a city whose destiny was decreed by @wDN{An} and @wDN{Enlil}, the primeval city, the beloved city of @wDN{Ninlil}?”}

@(A.255 = 255-263) The sorcerer answered her: @q[Ur-jiri-nuna,Sajburu]{“I went there without knowing all about this. I acknowledge your superiority -- please do not be bitter.”} He pleaded, he prayed to her: @q[Ur-jiri-nuna,Sajburu]{“Set me free, my sister; set me free. Let me go in peace to my city. Let me return safely to @wSN{Aratta}, the mount of the lustrous @fsux{me}. I will 
{make known
} {@noteanchor{1 ms. has instead:} declare
}  your greatness in all the lands. I will sing your praise in @wSN{Aratta}, the mount of the lustrous me.”}


@(A.264 = 264-273) Wise Woman @wPN{Saŋburu} answered to him: @q[Sajburu,Ur-jiri-nuna]{“You have caused distress in the animal pen and the byre; you have made the butter and milk scarce there. You have removed the lunch-table, the morning- and evening-table. You have cut off butter and milk from the evening meal of the great dining hall, ……… distress ……. Your sin that butter and milk …… cannot be forgiven. @wDN{Nanna} the king …… the byre …… milk; …… established that it was a capital offence and I am not pardoning your life.”} Wise Woman @wPN{Saŋburu} …… her decision about the sorcerer in the assembly (?). She threw her prisoner from the bank of the @wWN{Euphrates}. She seized from him his life-force and then returned to her city, @wSN{Ereš}.

@(A.274 = 274-280) Having heard this matter, @wRN{En-suḫgir-ana} sent a man to @wRN{Enmerkar}: @q[En-suhgir-ana,Enmerkar]{“You are the beloved lord of @wDN{Inana}, you alone are exalted. @wDN{Inana} has truly chosen you for her holy lap, you are her beloved. From the south to the highlands, you are the great lord, and I am only second to you; from the moment of conception I was not your equal, you are the older brother. I cannot match you ever.”}

@(A.281 = 281-283) In the contest between @wRN{Enmerkar} and @wRN{En-suḫgir-ana}, @wRN{Enmerkar} proved superior to @wRN{En-suḫgir-ana}. @wDN{Nisaba}, be praised!


